<br>
A possible abuse would be if the pets don't need to be in melee before summoning.  Mage parks pet in safe area, gets a sneaky or FD class to target something large protected by many guards.  Mage gets target from that person, says /pet attack, pet summons mob, battle ensues.  If the mob first must have damage dealt/recieved by the pet, then this potential for abuse drops to negligible levels.<br>
<br>
They had at least considered a mage anti-summon shield, why not test an ability to summon monsters, tied to a pet so they are actually useful (not to mention permitted) in a raid scenario?<br>
<br>
The ability to summon can be toggled for 50+ mobs, so regardless of the summon ability or not, I think adding levels would be a nice adjustment for pet usefulness.  Perhaps a buff spell as opposed to a default raising of pet levels; the spell need not be level 60, or overly rare, perhaps a level 55-57 spell that raises a pet by 5 - 8 levels, not neccessarily any other bonuses.  Alternatively, change Burnout to raise pet levels, dependent on the Burnout spell used (Burnout = no boost, II = 1 or 2 levels, III = 3 to 5 levels, IV = 5 to 7 levels).  This would only increase the pet's usefulness in high level encounters, without causing any issues on lower level mages.  Using my examples above, a level 60 mage using epic and BO4 would be able to make a level 56 pet, which would be more effective in combat against the raid-level mobs he's likely to encounter.  Myself, at level 57, using only BO3 on epic pet, would have a 53 or 54 epic pet.  Still useful, and will pick up less collateral aggro from green mobs.<br>
<br>
To quote MST3K's Joel: &quot;What do you think, Sirs?&quot; <p><p align=center><IMG SRC=http://www.chaac.com/aurelin/Fazzsig.jpg width="365" height="294"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueiago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/02 5:13:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic pet vs...</span><hr size=1> My paly puts out 60 - 100 dps.    Those numbers seem very low <p><b>Eiago X'ul Octavious <br>
